# What EAS uploads for mobile builds (eas build runs from app/mobile-app).
# Two jobs:
#
# 1. Hide the pnpm workspace markers. The EAS builder resolves the package
#    manager from lockfiles at the workspace root; this repo's root only has
#    pnpm-lock.yaml (the mobile app is a standalone npm project, NOT a pnpm
#    member), which older builder logic treats as "no lockfile" and DEFAULTS TO
#    YARN — crashing on the app's `"packageManager": "npm@10.9.2"` field.
#    Without these files in the upload, every builder version sees the app dir's
#    package-lock.json and installs with npm.
/package.json
/pnpm-lock.yaml
/pnpm-workspace.yaml

# 2. Keep the upload small: the mobile build only needs app/mobile-app itself,
#    the file:-dep packages, and the server GraphQL schemas for codegen
#    (eas-build-post-install runs `npm run codegen` against
#    ../../server/src/modules/**/*.schema.ts).
/portals/
/website/
/app/mweb/
/deploy/
/.github/
/docs/
/build/
# (server/ stays in — codegen reads server/src/modules/**/*.schema.ts and the
# whole server source is only a few MB; EAS's ignore impl doesn't support
# gitignore-style re-include negations reliably.)
